Part I - Ford-Go-Bike, Bike-Sharing System¶

by LEONE ARINA¶

Introduction¶

This data set includes information about individual rides made on the Ford-Go-Bike bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area for month of February 2019. This dataset includes 519,700 trips with 15 features entailing the users from their Birth Year, User Type, Duration of Ride, Start station, Start Location and Gender among may others.

What are the Issues with the dataset?¶

  1. Some data types are wrong
  2. A number of null values
  3. Needs an age column
  4. Duration will be easier to manage in minutes than Seconds thus has to be changed
  5. Creating a start day Column

Univariate Exploration¶

This section investigates the distributions of individual variables

In [17]:
def pie(p,t):
    sorted_counts = df[p].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=[10,7])
    plt.pie(sorted_counts, labels = sorted_counts.index, startangle = 90,autopct='%.2f', counterclock = False);
    plt.axis('square')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right');
    plt.title(t,fontsize=16);

#bar function
def bar(a,b,c):
    plt.figure(figsize=[14, 7]);
    base_color = sb.color_palette()[0]
    sb.countplot(data=df, x=a, color=base_color, order= df[a].value_counts().index)
    plt.xlabel(b, fontsize=14)
    plt.ylabel('Count', fontsize=14)
    plt.title(c,fontsize=16);

In [23]:
#Creating a Histogram plot function
def hist(a,b,c):
    binsize = 5
    bins = np.arange(0, df[a].max()+binsize, binsize)
    plt.figure(figsize=[10, 5])
    plt.hist(data = df, x = a ,bins=bins)
    plt.xlabel(b, size='14')
    plt.ylabel('Count ', size='14')
    plt.axis([-10, 140, 0, 70000])
    plt.title(c, size='14')

plt.ylabel("Frequency", size='14');

This shows that Youths were the majority of the users with very few eldely individuals(Thode above the age of 65)

  1. Yes there a rider who is 140 years old. I found this a bit odd asSomeone that old being able to ride a bike is pretty hard.
  2. I reoved the null values, changed datatypes, created new columns:'age','duration_minute'

It can be seen that the day of the week has no major to the ride duration as all the days seem to have the same distribution in ride duration

Where there interesting interactions between the variables?¶

The service seems to have the same pattern in terms of age and ride duration everyday of the week.

Conclusions¶

  1. There is a more demand for the service during the week as compared to weekends where the demand drops. This may be that most hire the bikes on working days so ast to beat traffic.
  2. Most of the users are Subscribers comming accounting for 90.53% of the total Users
  3. Most of the users are males accounting for 74.59
  4. Most of the users are the Youth foloowed by Adults then Teenagers and then the Elderly.
  5. Average age of most users was between 20-45years.
  6. The average ride duration for Other genders was higher then followed by females and finaly the males
  7. Most rides durations were averagly between 0-25minutes

Limitations¶

The data provided was only for the month of February and thus may not depict the true parterns all year round.
